@node "Intro_FEATURES" "The features of COMPACT"
Welcome to a new version of my player for audio CDs! It's name is "COMPACT",
which stands for "Comfortable Organizing and Music Playing AudioCD-Tool".
Is is written in Amiga-E V3.3a, and i tried to make it 100% system-conform,
so it should run also on future releases of the Amiga-OS.

Originally i wrote the player only for myself, because my real CD-player was
damaged and i thought about creating my own player for the Amiga, and as a
side-effect learning many things about how to do this. In the course of time,
more and more people wanted to get it, and so i began to extend its features
with the goal to make all my good ideas become real in this program.


@{U}And here are the main features:@{UU}

  - AGA / OS3.x compatible.  100% system conform (i hope so), and therefore
    it runs completely in the multitasking environment.

  - All basic functions of a real CD-player are available (plus many more).

  - Can run on a public screen (like the Workbench) or an own custom screen.
    @{B}On the own custom screen a BACKGROUND PICTURE (IFF) can be loaded
    behind the gadgets, with optionally switching on/off a colour-cycling
    effect@{UB}.

  - AppIcon and AppWindow feature for fast loading background pictures to
    the own custom screen.

  - Ability to jump from one public screen to an other while the player
    is running.

  - Optionally runs in the background (commodity) and @{B}can be controlled by
    hotkeys from nearly every program, without the need to activate the
    window of the player (SKIP, SEARCH, PLAY, PAUSE etc.)@{UB}!

  - Ability to open multiple windows, which can always remain opened. This
    includes the ONLINE-HELP window too.

  - With the zoom-gadget you can switch between a very small gui and the
    normal layout.

  - @{B}Built-in database for getting a quick overview of all your CDs. Also
    you can search for titles, track-names, CD length etc., and you can
    output selected data to a file or a printer.@{UB}

  - Analysis of the most heard CDs (TOP10), with graphical statistic display
    of the lengths of the CD-tracks.

  - ARexx-port available for external control.

  - @{B}Proportional gadget for easy access in four different modes@{UB}

  - Offers 10 bookmarks to mark important positions and jump directly to it
    at any time.

  - Recognizes CDs with an unique identnumber.

  - Has a program mode, in which you can define the tracks and its sequence
    you want to hear. Optionally it is possible to link a program to a CD,
    and everytime you insert this CD, your favorite program for this CD will
    be loaded too. This also works with the "Play after Start" option.
@endnode

@node "Intro_CDPLAYER" "What you need to run it"
To run COMPACT on your machine, you need the following things:

  - An Amiga ;-)
  - Amiga-OS 3.0 or higher (AGA chipset is NOT needed, but supported)
  - 1 MB free RAM or more
  - A CDROM-drive which can play audio CDs (almost all drives can do this)


Machines used for testings:

  - Amiga 1200 with OS3.1, Blizzard 1230-IV  68030 board with 50 MHz,
    68882-FPU 50 MHz, 8 MB Fastmem, 2 MB Chipmem, 120 MB Harddisk,
    Archos Overdrive CDROM-drive (double speed) connected to PCMCIA-port
    (driver version 11.2)

  - Amiga 1200 with OS3.0, 2 MB Chipmem, 420 MB Harddisk, Archos Overdrive
    CDROM-drive (quadro speed) connected to PCMCIA-port (driver version 11.2)

  - Amiga 4000 with OS3.1, 68030 with 25 MHz, 20 MB Fastmem, 2MB Chipmem,
    1 GB Harddisk, Sony CDU 76 SCSI CDROM-drive (quadrospeed), connected to
    Fastlane Z3 controller.


@{U}@{B}IMPORTANT NOTE:@{UU}@{UB}

I can not guarantee that the player will work on _EVERY_ CDROM drive, because
i have only a few drives available for testing. Of course you can choose,
which device-name and unit will be used, and in most cases it will work. But
if you own a drive, which does NOT work with the player, you should NOT send
me money for the registration, because i am not able to solve this problem!
Sorry about this, but it is nearly impossible for me to make your drive
working with my player, so if your drive is one of these, please try to use
an other player program!
@endnode

