@node "End_FAQS" "FAQ (Frequently asked questions)"
Q: @{B}Why isn't the HAM mode useable with non-AGA chipset?@{UB}

A: The HAM mode (HAM6) on non-AGA machines is only useable in the lowres
   mode (320 pixels per line), but COMPACT always needs the highres mode
   with 640 pixels per line, which is only available for HAM under AGA.
   For the same reason you can only use pictures with up to 16 colours on
   non-AGA Amigas, because 32 colours are only available in the lowres mode.


Q: @{B}When i choose the "own custom screen" mode, and the background picture
   has a high Y-size resolution (for example 640x512), COMPACT uses the
   font Topaz.8, which isn't good readable at this resolution. Why is it so?@{UB}

A: COMPACT tries to load the font "Helvetica 18" at the start. When it can't
   find it, Topaz.8 will be used instead. The Helvetica font is included
   with Workbench 3.0, so it should already be installed in your FONTS:
   drawer. If not, you should find it on your original Workbench 3.0 disks.


Q: @{B}It appears from time to time that the player stops without any reason.
   This mostly appears after the CD is playing for approximately 10 to 15
   minutes. I am using the AmiCDROM filesystem V1.15. How can i correct this?@{UB}

A: Under this filesystem version of AmiCDROM it can appear, that the play
   routine isn't working correctly. It is recommended to install the newer
   version of this filesystem (the newest version who is known to the author
   at the time of this writing is V2.36). It can be found for example on
   the CD "Meeting Pearls 4" in the directory ":Pearls/CDRom/AmiCDFS2" and
   with this version the problem mentioned above should not appear anymore.
   If the problem is not disappearing with the new version of the filesystem,
   you can try the menu @{"Settings / Start at every track" LINK m2ever}.
@endnode

@node "End_TIPS" "Hints and tricks"
- To reduce the size of the executable of COMPACT, you can compress it with
  a tool like for example Imploder V4.0 (Aminet:Util/Pack/), which reduces
  the size with a gain of approximate 70% !!

- Good background IFF-pictures for the own custom screen can be found for
  example in the directory "backgrounds" of the "SCALA MM300"-package, which
  was included in the A1200 distribution from Amiga Technologies. Also you
  can use for example fractal programs like ChaosPro (Aminet:Gfx/Fract/) to
  produce background pictures with a colour-cycling palette.
@endnode

@node "End_BUGS" "Known bugs"
No program is 100% error-free, and this also is valid for COMPACT. The
following things are known, but so far i couldn't find out the error in
the sourcecode:

- From time to time it happens, that COMPACT doesn't react on a command to
  continue playing at an other position, for example by pressing SKIP or
  by moving the proportional slider. The time display changes very short,
  but after that, it goes back to the old playing position. When the same
  command is choosen again, all things will be like they should be.

- In very very seldom circumstances it can appear, that the number of the
  tracks on CD will be displayed as -1, and then no reasonable work is
  possible with the player anymore. This error appeared only three times at
  the Amiga of my beta test person. I never have seen it by myself.

- Sometimes there is a very short interruption of the multitasking
  noticeable, which appears every second. When this effect is active, it is
  more noticeable in the "STOPPED"-mode than in the mode "PLAYING" or
  "PAUSED". You can see this effect for example, when a screen blanker is
  active which draws lines etc. to the screen.


If you find bugs not listed above, or you have a good idea about how to
remove an existing bug, you can contact me at my @{"home address" LINK Intro_Author}.
@endnode

@node "End_TODO" "The ToDo-List"
- Font sensitivity for all windows.

- Support for the Locale-library, including a german documentation too.

- Using BOOPSI-gadgets instead of the gadtools-library, so there could be
  graphics in the gadgets instead of pure text.

- Loading every picture format as a background for own custom screens by
  using datatypes. Eventually enabling background pictures also on the
  normal window display on the Workbench.

- Support for all screen modes / resolutions in the own custom screen mode.

- Support for index-marks on the CD (Index+ / Index-)

- Saving the database as a big single file instead of many small files. This
  new file can be used always, so there will be no need anymore to store all
  the small ID files to disk.

- Controlling the volume via a slider gadget, and perform fade in / fade out.

- Display the player with user definable skins would give the user full
  control of the layout of COMPACTs graphical user interface.
@endnode

@node "End_HISTORY" "History"
All versions between V1.00 and V1.38 are only internal versions, which were
never released to the public, so they are not listed here separately.


@{B}@{U}Notes to V1.40:@{UU}@{UB}

After more than 1 year i finally released an update of the player (V1.40).
I wanted to do this at the latest in the middle of 2000, but with a few of
the new things i wanted to implement, there were many unexpected problems
occured, which aren't easy to solve. A few of these ideas haven't therefore
found the way into the player until now, and the ToDo-list isn't become as
small as i wanted it to be.

But i decided to release an update now for two reasons:
  1. A relatively small update is better than nothing, and the currently
     registered people can use it without paying money, because their keyfile
     will make the shareware version to a full working version.
  2. Because of the problems i mentioned above, and the fact that i don't
     have as much time available for developing as i need, it is unlikely
     that i can implement all the good things in the NEAR future. Surely, i
     plan to improve COMPACT with the things of my ToDo-list, but the job
     in my firm is an important part too, that i can't neglect.

Well, i hope you will have fun with this new version of COMPACT, and hopefully
you will enjoy the new features of it.



V1.40	- Second release (02/2001)
	- For every CD there will be stored, how often it is heard, and the
	  date it is first / last heard. This information can be displayed
	  by the user, or it can be used to create a @{"statistic (TOP10)" LINK Statisti}.
	  @{I}(Please read the note there at the bottom of the side)@{UI}
	- In a new window the statistic of the TOP10 can be viewed, and
	  also there is a graphical display of the lengths of the CD-tracks.
	  Here exists also the ability to reset the counter of one/all CDs
	  to zero (it counts how often the CD is heard), and to synchronize
	  the TOP10 file with the database.
	- Fixed a few small bugs in the behavior of the program. Also
	  optimized a few routines for faster working (database).
	- Enhanced the installer script. When installing a new version of the
	  program over an existing one, the files which contains user defined
	  settings will be backuped before overwriting (the icon of COMPACT
	  with its tooltypes, compact.config and compact.db).

V1.39	- The modes of the color cycling effect are now saved along with the
	  config-file.
	- The data of the registered user will now always be correctly
	  left aligned, when displayed in the registration window.

V1.38	- First release (11/1999).

V1.00	- First working version with only the most important functions
	  included.
@endnode

