@node "showdevices" "A small tool to show all available devices"
You can start this program from the shell only, so please open a shell
and change the actual path to the drawer in which COMPACT is stored. Then
type in only "showdevices" and you will get a list of all available device-
names in your system, which could be useable for a CD-Rom (audio.device etc.
won't be included in the list).

The program "showdevices" is (c) Copyright 1997-2001 by Ralph Weisel. It is
distributed as freeware.
It may be freely distributed as long as it remains unchanged (archiving
and packing allowed).

The same conditions as mentioned in the chapter @{"DISCLAIMER" LINK "Intro_DISCLAIMER" 35} are valid for
this program, so please read there. The author is not responsible for any
appearing errors or anything else!
@endnode
